main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted in the Far East, alternating between white, green, and red lights.
interesting points: The object was very distinct and bright, fading into the clouds twice before reappearing at varying altitudes.
The light faded at 191524Z, but the speed and direction of travel were not determined.
The sighting lasted for approximately 15 minutes.
The object was sighted by a military source at the location of 34-22N 163-45E.
The report is from Project Blue Book, the official U.S. Air Force program that investigated UFOs from 1947 to 1969.
sighted object: a bright, alternating light that faded in and out of the clouds
